item.title: Thumb splint
item.description:
DISCLAIMER: If you suffer some kind of arm or finger injury, seek medical attention; never self diagnose yourself whithout proper medical training.

This is a simple 3 piece thumb splint for emergency use; to keep it from moving avoid further damage. It's not very comfortable or incredibly well designed; but it is fast to print an does the job (roughly 1:30-2 hours with a 6mm nozzle). To assemble it, glue the 3 pieces together in whichever distance you find most comfortable; or re- scale to fit your arm (this design was meant for a hand that, from the wrist to the tip of the middle finger, is 19cm). To atach it to the arm, you can really use anything; but electrical tape or similar dhesives work just fine. Avoid using rubber bands; they can easily reduce blood flow if they are too tight.

Please, feel free to remix or improve the design so others can use it

item.title: Rimzler Dison CineWhoop 3 Inch frame gopro mount top plate
item.description:
This top-plate for the Rimzler Dison CineWhoop 3 Inch frame has a built-in gopro-style mounting bracket and holes for a battery strap and mounting screws.

Print it in something rigid, not TPU. Good materials are: PLA+Carbon Fiber, and PLA.

Use the plate screw holes to drill into the frame with a 1.5mm drill bit. 3-24x3/8" self-tapping screws work well.

With this setup, I get 4 minutes of flight time from an 850mah battery with a Hero9 camera.

item.description:

item.title: Voron 0 - Sherpa Mini Mount
item.description:
This is a Sherpa Mini Mount for the Voron 0.1 3D Printer. The Sherpa Mini being quite a close fit to the stock Mini Afterburner makes this a very practical alternative for the Voron.0.1 with the added bonus of less clogging, easier maintenance and much better visual access to potential maintenance issues. IMHO the Sherpa having SLS printed parts may make this an improved long term option.

Dragon & Dragonfly Hot End options uploaded.

Printed & working but not Fully Tested yet so WIP.

I have uploaded a step file of the parts for customisation.

Test Video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=82DchNpkh2E

Installation Printing Notes

1.Please refer to the General Assembly PDF for required Fixings.
2.No parts require support if printed in the uploaded orientation. The RH Fan duct will require the integrated support to the bolt fix to be removed.
3.Printed with Hatchbox Black ABS.

item.description:
This is a small box for mounting an TCRT5000 IR Barrier sensor on a LGB gauche G train track. Design of the mount bracket is a small adjustment of https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2775166?collect and compatible to Stante's (https://www.thingiverse.com/Stante) other designs. item.title: Cable strain relief
item.description:
Printed a smoothieboard enclosure for the Bear / MK3S clone I was building (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2104547) and needed a way to feed the print bed cable and main power cable to the board. Enclosure had a couple 19.5 mm holes in the design, so created a strain relief that'll snap in. Has a couple notches along the body for zip ties to lock down the cables.

I used some TPU I had sitting around, which worked great and gives some flex. Other filaments should work, but I'd consider cutting infill to allow a bit of flex on the fingers that snap into the hole.

The Tauminator has arrived! Combining the absolute cutting edge technology from the Space Communists and the most powerful armor of the humans, one of the most powerful warriors in the galaxy was created. item.title: Beach Walker
item.description:
This is a special crutch cap that can be put on and taken off a crutch or walking stick. The cap has a bigger surface so the user of these caps can walk on soft terrain.The spacers have to be fixed with the following:

  • DIN 934 nuts M3
  • DIN 7991 bolts M3x8mm

The beach walker itself has a tube on the outside and this is used to fix the beach walker to the spacers. To fix the beach walker you need a hose clamp that has an inner diameter of 55 mm.

This thing is invented for people with walking disabilities or those who don't have the strength to walk as much anymore to be able to walk on soft terrains like beaches or trails.

If you want to print this and make it functional then it is recommended you print this with nylon (PA 12) and use an SLS printer. FDM printing can be used but it won't be as strong as SLS printing.

item.title: (WIP) Samsung Galaxy S8 g950 case
item.description:
This is a work in progress, the case could not fit on your phone. This test case was made for the regular Samsung Galaxy S8; for the S8+ see this; and for the S8 Active see this. For different reasons, I have trouble to test some of the phone cases I have designed. So that, I left the cases uploaded; in case anyone wants to help me testing them. I would really appreciate any feedback on the models. I will need:
  • Photos of the phone with the case printed.
  • The material you used, that could be PLA, ABS, PETG, HIPS or Nylon, but not flexible filaments.
  • The exact model of your phone. In this case can be G950F, G950FD, G950U, G950A, G950P, G950T, G950V, G950R4, G950W, G950S, G950K, G950L or G9500.
  • A description of how it fits.
Once I have a tested ok model I will publish the final versions for rigid and flexible materials, of course crediting my testers.
For other phone cases check this.

  • GSMArena
